  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-10 clean negative control)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This negative-control package is structurally complete and fully clean: all 13 credibility factors are assessed with achievedLevel >= requiredLevel, all ValidationResults carry comparedAgainst and uncertainty links, the provenance chain is complete, and the decision record is grounded in structured evidence. No weakener should fire on this package.",
