        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the Navier-Stokes and scalar transport (hemolysis) equations. Observed order of accuracy must be within 10% of formal order for all tested norms. All known code defects affecting the QoI must be resolved."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification performed on all governing equations including the hemolysis power-law transport scalar. Observed spatial order of accuracy is 1.97 (formal: 2.0) for velocity and 1.94 for hemolysis scalar — within the 10% tolerance. Temporal MMS confirms second-order accuracy. All defects affecting hemolysis QoI are resolved. Gradation 4 achieved and required."
