        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Richardson extrapolation-based Grid Convergence Index (GCI) must be <2% for pressure-head and <5% for hemolysis index QoIs on the production mesh. Three systematically refined meshes with refinement ratio >= 1.3 required."
      },
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (4.2 M, 11.8 M, 31.4 M cells; refinement ratio ~1.41) used for GCI study. GCI on pressure head: 0.8%; GCI on NIH: 3.1%. Both within acceptance thresholds. Production mesh is the 11.8 M cell intermediate mesh, providing adequate accuracy at feasible computational cost. Gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
