        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Quantitative comparison metrics (RMSE, normalised error) must be computed for all QoIs across all 5 operating points. Comparison must account for experimental uncertainty using U95 intervals. Hemolysis NIH predictions must fall within ±15% of measured values at all operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH predictions at all 5 operating points fall within 9.3% of measured values (maximum deviation). Pressure-head RMSE is 0.8% of the operating range. Comparison accounts for experimental U95 uncertainty bands derived from repeated experimental runs (n=5 per operating point). Quantitative validation metrics are documented in the Morrison 2024 validation report. Gradation 4 achieved and required."
    },
    {
