        "description": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, pressure head) must be demonstrated to be the same quantities used in the regulatory submission decision. A documented traceability matrix linking clinical hemolysis threshold to NIH QoI must exist."
      },
      "rationale": "A formal QoI traceability matrix links the FDA hemolysis acceptance criterion (NIH < 0.01 g/100 L) directly to the computed and measured NIH values. Pressure head is a secondary QoI confirming overall hydraulic performance. Both QoIs are identical between validation activities and the COU decision. Gradation 4 achieved and required."
