        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou2-modelform",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The turbulence model, hemolysis power-law model, and non-Newtonian rheology assumptions must each be justified with literature evidence or sensitivity analysis. Alternative model forms must be considered and the selection rationale documented."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on literature evidence for rotating machinery hemolysis prediction (Bludszuweit 1995, Garon & Farinas 2004). Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen et al.) justified against two alternative formulations (Zhang et al., Taskin et al.) via sensitivity analysis showing <8% NIH variation. Newtonian approximation justified for glycerol-water analogue. All selection rationales documented. Gradation 4 achieved and required."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-modelinputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
