        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, hemolysis model constants, turbulence model coefficients) must have documented sources with uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input uncertainty through to QoI uncertainty intervals."
      },
      "rationale": "All 14 model input parameters are documented with sources and uncertainty bounds (literature or measurement). Monte Carlo UQ (n=2000 samples, Latin hypercube sampling) propagates input uncertainty to NIH and pressure-head QoIs. 95% prediction intervals for NIH are ±11% of nominal at the most sensitive operating point. Input uncertainty dominates over discretization error, confirming the UQ is the binding credibility activity. Gradation 4 achieved and required."
    },
